# BUG REPRODUCTION: Array Index Normalization Failure
# Logstash arrays can be accessed using `field[0][name]`. The analyzer attempts
# to normalize this to `field.0.name`, but the regex `^\[([^\]]+)\]$` fails because
# `field` is outside the brackets. The string remains unnormalized, causing a
# total disconnect in static queries for `field.0.name`.
# EXPECTED FIX: `user[0][name]` should be normalized to `user.0.name`.
filter {
  mutate { replace => { "user[0][name]" => "Alice" } }
}
